Resets the stateset to be as if it started on the passed node. This should be called for all initial statesets.

isSubset

boolean isSubset(StateSetType other)
Queries whether this stateset is a subset of another, in other words, if every state inhabited by this set is also inhabited by the other. Another way of thinking about this is that merging 'this' into 'other' does not affect other when this is a subset.

Parameters:
other - The set to compare against - superset, if result is true.
Returns:
If this is a subset of other.
